        npx @erwininteractive/mvc init myapp --with-ci
      </code>
      <p class="text-terminal-fg mb-4 text-sm">
        Or add CI to an existing project by creating <code class="bg-terminal-dim bg-opacity-20 rounded px-1 py-0.5 text-xs">.github/workflows/test.yml</code>:
      </p>
      <code class="block bg-terminal-dim bg-opacity-20 rounded p-3 text-terminal-fg text-xs">
        name: Test<br/><br/>
        on:<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;push:<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;branches: [main]<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;pull_request:<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;branches: [main]<br/><br/>
        jobs:<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;test:<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;runs-on: ubuntu-latest<br/><br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;steps:<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- name: Checkout<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;uses: actions/checkout@v4<br/><br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- name: Setup Node.js<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;uses: actions/setup-node@v4<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;with:<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;node-version: "20"<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;cache: "npm"<br/><br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- name: Install dependencies<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;run: npm ci<br/><br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- name: Run tests<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;run: npm test<br/><br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- name: Build<br/>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;run: npm run build
      </code>
      <p class="text-terminal-fg mt-4 text-sm">
        See full documentation on <a href="https://github.com/erwininteractive/typescript-erwinmvc#readme" class="text-terminal-cyan hover:text-terminal-green" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> for database tests, secrets, and more.
